      <description>YALE ENVIRONMENT 360: Subsistence hunters in the Arctic have long taken to the sea ice to hunt seals, whales and polar bears. But now, as the ice disappears and soaring temperatures alter the life cycles and abundance of their prey, a growing number of indigenous communities face food shortages.</description>
